                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18390708-2128-offence-1 t18390708-name-682"></join>Griffith Thomas</persName>, in his dwelling-house.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390708-name-683" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-683" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-683" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-683" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>MISS. ANN THOMAS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live with my brother, Griffith Thomas, at Den<lb></lb>mark-hill, Surrey. On the 9th of July, between ten and two o'clock in the day, I was passing the dining-room door, and saw a sweep at the side<lb></lb>board drawer—it was the prisoner—he had no business there—when he saw me, he ran to the closet and hid himself—I called for assistance—he remained in the closet till my brother came to him, and he took six silver cups out of the cupboard—they were never kept there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390708-name-684" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-684" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-684" type="surname" value="STOCK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-684" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>ROBERT STOCK</persName>
                  </hi>. On the 9th of July, I was at Mr. Thomas's house. I went into the dining-room, and saw the prisoner hiding himself in the closet, and saw these cups there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390708-name-685" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-685" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-685" type="surname" value="SIMMS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-685" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH SIMMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am servant to Mr. Thomas. These are his cups—I had seen them that day in the dining-room drawer at ten o'clock—they had no business in the cupboard—the prisoner had no business there—they are worth above 10<hi rend="italic">l</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was looking after work—I knocked at the door—nobody answered—the doors were wide open—I then knocked at the parlour door—nobody answered—I knocked again, and I was at the door when the lady came out of the other room door—I was more in the door than out, as it was wide open—I was not in the cupboard at all—I wanted to know if the chimneys wanted sweeping.</p>
